### Implement Manual Cache Management with getCache in Vercel Functions

Source: https://context7.com/vercel/vercel/llms.txt

Uses getCache API to manually store and retrieve cached responses with custom cache keys. Checks cache before generating expensive data, stores successful responses, and returns cached data on subsequent requests. Provides fine-grained control over cache lifecycle.

```javascript
import { getCache } from '@vercel/functions';

export async function GET(request) {
  const cache = getCache();
  const cacheKey = new URL(request.url).pathname;

  // Try to get from cache
  const cached = await cache.match(cacheKey);
  if (cached) {
    return cached;
  }

  // Generate response
  const data = await generateExpensiveData();
  const response = Response.json(data, {
    headers: {
      'Cache-Control': 's-maxage=300',
    },
  });

  // Store in cache
  await cache.put(cacheKey, response.clone());

  return response;
}
```
